SIMPLE: spinetail
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spinetail
<hw>Spine"tail`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Any one or several species of swifts of the genus
<gen>Acanthylis</gen>, or <gen>Chaetura</gen>, and allied genera, in
which the shafts of the tail feathers terminate in rigid spines.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any one of several species of South American and
Central American clamatorial birds belonging to <gen>Synallaxis</gen>
and allied genera of the family <fam>Dendrocolaptidae</fam>. They are
allied to the ovenbirds.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>The ruddy duck.</def>
<mark>[Local, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spine-tailed</ent>⟦br⟧
